The '''Deneba bush''' was a [[:Category:Predatory creatures|predatory]] [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Bush/Legends|bush]] that was native to [[Deneba/Legends|Deneba]]. A [[Sentience/Legends|semi-sentient]] [[Plant/Legends|plant]] that disguised itself as a [[Tree/Legends|tree]] in order to lure its prey, the bush would pick up [[Death/Legends|dead]], discarded leaves and hold them on its branches. Unwary passersby would soon find themselves the object of the plant's next meal.

Its leafy disguise worked so well that, in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], one of the bushes was able to take by surprise and, before the hapless henchman could scream, devour the [[Dug/Legends|Dug]] mercenary [[Khiss (Dug)|Khiss]] in [[Gardulla Besadii the Elder/Legends|Gardulla's]] [[Gardulla's pleasure garden|pleasure garden]], within the walls of [[Gardulla the Hutt's Palace/Legends|her palace]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], near the [[Dune Sea/Legends|Dune Sea]].

